{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875911465,"sessionID":"ses_2858d638affemr61pumzKHgw4C","part":{"id":"prt_d7a73e7f3001eT1RwsEQVLKU08","messageID":"msg_d7a73d00f00102yAqoD1cgwVeP","sessionID":"ses_2858d638affemr61pumzKHgw4C","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3a773150411c42c2b3613ea4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-033\n4: - **Module**: root\n5: - **Language**: Makefile\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The Makefile serves as the central build orchestration layer for the AgentCube project, providing a unified CLI interface for all development, build, test, and deployment operations. It bridges Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing workflows, and development environment management under a consistent `make` interface.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Target Hierarchy\n16: \n17: ```\n18: Makefile\n19: ├── Configuration Variables\n20: │   ├── DOCKER_REGISTRY, DOCKER_TAG, GO_VERSION, BINARY_VERSION\n21: │   └── BINARIES, GO_LDFLAGS, BUILD_FLAGS\n22: │\n23: ├── Binary Build Targets (Primary)\n24: │   ├── build              # Default: build all binaries\n25: │   ├── build-router\n26: │   ├── build-workload-manager\n27: │   ├── build-agentd\n28: │   └── build-picod\n29: │\n30: ├── Cross-Compilation Targets\n31: │   ├── cross-build        # All platforms\n32: │   ├── build-linux-amd64\n33: │   ├── build-linux-arm64\n34: │   ├── build-darwin-amd64\n35: │   └── build-darwin-arm64\n36: │\n37: ├── Docker Build Targets (AR-032)\n38: │   ├── docker-build\n39: │   ├── docker-build-router\n40: │   ├── docker-build-workload-manager\n41: │   ├── docker-build-agentd\n42: │   ├── docker-push\n43: │   └── validate-dockerfiles\n44: │\n45: ├── Test Targets\n46: │   ├── test              # Default: test-unit\n47: │   ├── test-unit\n48: │   └── test-cover\n49: │\n50: ├── Code Quality Targets\n51: │   ├── lint\n52: │   ├── lint-fix\n53: │   └── fmt\n54: │\n55: ├── Development Targets\n56: │   ├── dev               # Default: dev-docker\n57: │   └── dev-docker\n58: │\n59: ├── Cleanup Targets\n60: │   ├── clean\n61: │   └── docker-clean\n62: │\n63: └── Utility Targets\n64:     ├── help\n65:     ├── version\n66:     └── deps\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### 1.3 Component Responsibilities\n70: \n71: | Component | Responsibility |\n72: |-----------|----------------|\n73: | Binary Build | Compiles Go source to platform-specific executables |\n74: | Cross-Compile | Generates binaries for multiple OS/architecture combinations |\n75: | Docker Build | Invokes Docker build with multi-stage builds for minimal images |\n76: | Test | Executes unit tests with coverage reporting |\n77: | Lint/Format | Enforces code quality standards |\n78: | Development | Starts local development environment |\n79: | Utilities | Provides help, version info, dependency checking |\n80: \n81: ## 2. Data Structures\n82: \n83: ### 2.1 Configuration Variables\n84: \n85: ```makefile\n86: # Registry and versioning\n87: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= agentcube\n88: DOCKER_TAG      ?= latest\n89: GO_VERSION      ?= 1.24\n90: BINARY_VERSION  ?= dev\n91: \n92: # Binary configuration\n93: BINARIES := router workload-manager agentd picod\n94: GO_LDFLAGS := -s -w -X main.version=$(BINARY_VERSION)\n95: \n96: # Build configuration\n97: CGO_ENABLED := 0\n98: GOOS_DEFAULT := linux\n99: GOARCH_DEFAULT := amd64\n100: BUILD_DIR := bin\n101: \n102: # Test configuration\n103: TEST_FLAGS := -v -short\n104: COVERAGE_PROFILE := coverage.out\n105: COVERAGE_REPORT := coverage.html\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### 2.2 Target Categories\n109: \n110: | Category | Type | Description |\n111: |----------|------|-------------|\n112: | Binary targets | File-based | Produce binary executables in `bin/` |\n113: | Docker targets | Image-based | Produce Docker images |\n114: | Test targets | Process-based | Run test suites |\n115: | Utility targets | Informational | Display help/version |\n116: \n117: ### 2.3 Output Directory Structure\n118: \n119: ```\n120: bin/\n121: ├── router              # Linux amd64 (default)\n122: ├── workload-manager\n123: ├── agentd\n124: ├── picod\n125: ├── linux-amd64/\n126: │   ├── router\n127: │   ├── workload-manager\n128: │   ├── agentd\n129: │   └── picod\n130: ├── linux-arm64/\n131: ├── darwin-amd64/\n132: └── darwin-arm64/\n133: ```\n134: \n135: ## 3. API Contracts\n136: \n137: ### 3.1 Binary Build API\n138: \n139: #### `make build`\n140: \n141: - **Description**: Build all binaries for the current platform\n142: - **Parameters**: None (uses defaults)\n143: - **Output**: Creates `bin/{router,workload-manager,agentd,picod}`\n144: - **Flags**: `CGO_ENABLED=0`, ldflags with version injection\n145: - **Exit Code**: 0 on success, non-zero on failure\n146: \n147: #### `make build-<binary>`\n148: \n149: - **Description**: Build a specific binary\n150: - **Valid Targets**: `router`, `workload-manager`, `agentd`, `picod`\n151: - **Output**: Creates `bin/<binary>`\n152: - **Example**: `make build-router` → `bin/router`\n153: \n154: ### 3.2 Cross-Compilation API\n155: \n156: #### `make cross-build`\n157: \n158: - **Description**: Build for all supported platforms\n159: - **Output**: Creates `bin/{linux,darwin}-{amd64,arm64}/*`\n160: - **Targets**:\n161:   - `make build-linux-amd64` → `bin/linux-amd64/`\n162:   - `make build-linux-arm64` → `bin/linux-arm64/`\n163:   - `make build-darwin-amd64` → `bin/darwin-amd64/`\n164:   - `make build-darwin-arm64` → `bin/darwin-arm64/`\n165: \n166: ### 3.3 Docker Build API\n167: \n168: #### `make docker-build`\n169: \n170: - **Description**: Build all Docker images\n171: - **Output**: Images tagged as `{DOCKER_REGISTRY}-{component}:{DOCKER_TAG}` and `:latest`\n172: - **Dependencies**: Requires Docker daemon running\n173: \n174: #### `make docker-build-<component>`\n175: \n176: - **Valid Components**: `router`, `workload-manager`, `agentd`\n177: - **Output**: Single image built and tagged\n178: \n179: ### 3.4 Test API\n180: \n181: #### `make test`\n182: \n183: - **Description**: Run unit tests (default target)\n184: - **Flags**: `-v -short`\n185: - **Output**: Test results to stdout\n186: \n187: #### `make test-unit`\n188: \n189: - **Description**: Run only unit tests\n190: - **Flags**: `-v ./...`\n191: \n192: #### `make test-cover`\n193: \n194: - **Description**: Run tests with coverage\n195: - **Output**:\n196:   - `coverage.out` (raw profile)\n197:   - `coverage.html` (HTML report)\n198:   - Coverage percentage to stdout\n199: \n200: ### 3.5 Code Quality API\n201: \n202: #### `make lint`\n203: \n204: - **Description**: Run golangci-lint\n205: - **Flags**: `./...` (all packages)\n206: - **Exit Code**: Non-zero if lint errors found\n207: \n208: #### `make lint-fix`\n209: \n210: - **Description**: Run linter with auto-fix\n211: - **Flags**: `--fix`\n212: \n213: #### `make fmt`\n214: \n215: - **Description**: Format code\n216: - **Tools**: `gofmt -w -s`, `goimports -w`\n217: \n218: ### 3.6 Development API\n219: \n220: #### `make dev`\n221: \n222: - **Description**: Start development environment\n223: - **Default**: Invokes `dev-docker`\n224: \n225: #### `make dev-docker`\n226: \n227: - **Description**: Start services via docker-compose\n228: - **Command**: `docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d`\n229: \n230: ### 3.7 Utility API\n231: \n232: #### `make help`\n233: \n234: - **Description**: Display all available targets\n235: - **Format**: Categorized help text\n236: \n237: #### `make version`\n238: \n239: - **Description**: Display current build version\n240: - **Output**: `BINARY_VERSION` value\n241: \n242: #### `make deps`\n243: \n244: - **Description**: Verify required dependencies\n245: - **Checks**: Go, Docker, (optional) golangci-lint\n246: \n247: ### 3.8 Configuration Override API\n248: \n249: | Variable | Override Syntax | Default |\n250: |----------|----------------|---------|\n251: | Registry | `make DOCKER_REGISTRY=custom build` | `agentcube` |\n252: | Tag | `make DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0 build` | `latest` |\n253: | Version | `make BINARY_VERSION=1.0.0 build` | `dev` |\n254: | Go Version | `make GO_VERSION=1.23 docker-build` | `1.24` |\n255: \n256: ## 4. Error Handling\n257: \n258: ### 4.1 Dependency Errors\n259: \n260: #### Missing Go Installation\n261: \n262: ```\n263: Error: Go is required but not installed.\n264: Please install Go 1.24+: https://go.dev/dl/\n265: ```\n266: \n267: **Mitigation**: `make deps` checks Go availability before build targets.\n268: \n269: #### Missing Docker\n270: \n271: ```\n272: Error: Docker is required but not installed.\n273: Please install Docker: https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/\n274: ```\n275: \n276: **Mitigation**: `make deps` checks Docker availability.\n277: \n278: #### Missing Source Code\n279: \n280: ```\n281: go build: cannot load package: package ./cmd/router not found\n282: ```\n283: \n284: **Behavior**: Go's native error messages are propagated directly.\n285: \n286: ### 4.2 Build Failures\n287: \n288: | Scenario | Behavior | Exit Code |\n289: |----------|----------|-----------|\n290: | Binary compilation fails | Propagate go build error | Non-zero |\n291: | Docker build fails | Propagate docker error | Non-zero |\n292: | Test failure | Show test output | Non-zero |\n293: | Lint errors | Show lint report | Non-zero |\n294: \n295: ### 4.3 Cleanup Errors\n296: \n297: ```makefile\n298: docker-clean:\n299: \tdocker rmi $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)-router:$(DOCKER_TAG) ... 2>/dev/null || true\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Behavior**: Silently ignore missing images (using `|| true`).\n303: \n304: ### 4.4 Validation Errors\n305: \n306: ```makefile\n307: validate-dockerfiles:\n308: \tdocker build -f docker/base.Dockerfile --target builder --no-run . || \\\n309: \t\t(echo \"base.Dockerfile validation failed\" && exit 1)\n310: ```\n311: \n312: **Behavior**: Explicit error messages with context.\n313: \n314: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n315: \n316: ### 5.1 Unit Testing Targets\n317: \n318: | Target | Purpose | Verification |\n319: |--------|---------|--------------|\n320: | `make test` | Default test suite | All tests pass |\n321: | `make test-unit` | Unit tests only | `-short` flag skips integration |\n322: | `make test-cover` | Coverage analysis | Coverage ≥ 70% target |\n323: \n324: ### 5.2 Integration Testing\n325: \n326: ```makefile\n327: test-integration:\n328: \tgo test -v -tags=integration ./integration/...\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Requirement**: Tag-based test isolation (`-tags=integration`).\n332: \n333: ### 5.3 Makefile Target Testing\n334: \n335: | Scenario ID | Test Case | Verification Method |\n336: |------------|-----------|---------------------|\n337: | MAKE-001 | `make build` | Verify `bin/` contains all 4 binaries |\n338: | MAKE-002 | `make build-router` | Verify only `bin/router` exists |\n339: | MAKE-003 | `make cross-build` | Verify all 4 platform directories exist |\n340: | MAKE-004 | `make test` | Verify test output shows pass/fail |\n341: | MAKE-005 | `make lint` | Verify lint exits non-zero on errors |\n342: | MAKE-006 | `make fmt` | Verify code formatting applied |\n343: | MAKE-007 | `make help` | Verify help text displays |\n344: | MAKE-008 | `make clean` | Verify `bin/` removed |\n345: \n346: ### 5.4 Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n347: \n348: | Delta Spec ID | Acceptance Criteria | Test Method |\n349: |----------------|---------------------|-------------|\n350: | AR-033-001 | `make build` produces binaries | File existence check |\n351: | AR-033-010 | `make cross-build` all platforms | Directory structure check |\n352: | AR-033-011 | `make docker-build` | Image existence check |\n353: | AR-033-016 | `make test` | Test exit code |\n354: | AR-033-018 | `make test-cover` | Coverage file exists |\n355: | AR-033-019 | `make lint` | Non-zero on errors |\n356: | AR-033-026 | `make help` | Output contains target names |\n357: | AR-033-034 | Missing Go error | Error message check |\n358: \n359: ## 6. Implementation Notes\n360: \n361: ### 6.1 PHONY Targets\n362: \n363: All non-file targets declared as `.PHONY`:\n364: \n365: ```makefile\n366: .PHONY: build build-router build-workload-manager build-agentd build-picod\n367: .PHONY: cross-build build-linux-amd64 build-linux-arm64 build-darwin-amd64 build-darwin-arm64\n368: .PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-workload-manager docker-build-agentd\n369: .PHONY: test test-unit test-integration test-cover\n370: .PHONY: lint lint-fix fmt\n371: .PHONY: dev dev-docker\n372: .PHONY: clean docker-clean\n373: .PHONY: help version deps\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### 6.2 Platform Independence\n377: \n378: - Avoid shell-specific commands (`$(shell ...)` minimal usage)\n379: - Use Go's cross-platform compilation (`GOOS`, `GOARCH`)\n380: - Path separators: Use `/` (Make handles Windows conversion)\n381: \n382: ### 6.3 Self-Documenting\n383: \n384: Help target provides categorized output:\n385: \n386: ```\n387: AgentCube Makefile Targets\n388: \n389: Build:\n390:   make build              Build all binaries for current platform\n391:   make build-<binary>     Build specific binary (router|workload-manager|agentd|picod)\n392:   make cross-build        Build for all platforms\n393: \n394: Docker:\n395:   make docker-build       Build all Docker images\n396:   make docker-push        Push images to registry\n397: ...\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ## 7. Relationship to Other ARs\n401: \n402: | AR | Relationship |\n403: |----|--------------|\n404: | AR-032 | Docker multi-stage builds use this Makefile for binary compilation |\n405: | AR-030 | Helm chart deployment independent |\n406: | CI/CD Pipeline | Consumes `make build`, `make test`, `make docker-build` |\n407: \n408: ## 8. References\n409: \n410: - Proposal: `changes/AR-033/proposal.md`\n411: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md`\n412: - Existing Makefile: `Makefile`\n413: - Go Cross-Compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n414: - golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n\n(End of file - total 414 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-033\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe Makefile serves as the central build orchestration layer for the AgentCube project, providing a unified CLI interface for all development, build, test, and deployment operations. It bridges Go source compilation, Docker image building, testing workflows, and development environment management under a consistent `make` interface.\n\n### 1.2 Target Hierarchy\n\n```\nMakefile\n├── Configuration Variables\n│   ├── DOCKER_REGISTRY, DOCKER_TAG, GO_VERSION, BINARY_VERSION","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-033/design.md","time":{"start":1775875911451,"end":1775875911461}}}}
